ution

Dear Team, it was lovely meeting you last Friday!
Producing the translational process in the documents attached took me longe=
r than expected. Sigh!
I am requesting your feedback on the attached document, Convert Research in=
to a Business-Ready Solution, focusing on the "Research-to-Business Process=
 Table" and related "Guide."  R\Please return your completed feedback by 10=
 AM Friday August 15 - 1hr before we meet. We will discuss your feedback at=
 the meeting.
To make feedback consistent and easy to consolidate, please use the attache=
d Feedback Template (Research to Business Feedback Template.docx) to record=
 your comments.
Your feedback should cover the following areas:

  1.
Steps in the Process Table
     *
Are the activities for each step clear, actionable, and logically sequenced=
?
     *
Are any steps redundant or missing?
     *
Are the outputs for each step sufficiently specific and measurable?
  2.
AI Tools to Support Each Step
     *
Identify AI tools that could help execute each step efficiently (e.g., lite=
rature search, data synthesis, solution evaluation, presentation preparatio=
n).
     *
Where possible, name specific tools and describe how they would be applied.
  3.
Additional Observations (if applicable)
     *
Any terminology that may be unclear to students or company stakeholders.
     *
Suggestions to improve alignment with a 13-week project timeline.
     *
Opportunities to integrate real-world examples or templates for outputs.

Instructions:

  *
Open the feedback template.
  *
For each step listed in the first column, provide your comments in the seco=
nd column, list any AI tools in the third column, and add other notes in th=
e fourth column.
  *
Save the completed file with your name in the filename (e.g., Feedback_Temp=
late_YourName.docx).

Thank you for your contributions toward refining this process so it=92s bot=
h academically rigorous and practically useful for our "Up Our Game, Canada=
" projects.
See you Friday at 11 AM.
Best regards,
Tony B.


